# This file defines command aliases that will be available after sourcing.
# Aliases are loaded when you start a new shell or run 'mt reload'.
#
# NAMING CONVENTIONS:
#   - Use lowercase with hyphens: my-alias
#   - Keep names short and memorable
#   - Avoid overriding common commands unless intentional
#
# BEST PRACTICES:
#   - Use aliases for frequently-used command combinations
#   - Add a comment explaining what each alias does
#   - Group related aliases together
#   - Consider using functions for complex logic (see shell/functions)
#
# EXAMPLES:

